# call.word — the CALL verb, the do that wakes a being to act. Was summon.
# Descends from word.word, out.word, do.word, being.word, name.word. A do may act on a being as a body
# (do move, do set); that is no call. A call rouses the being to act as itself, through a Name
# that can act through it (its own, or an inhabitor). The host (seed/ibp/verbs/call.js) delivers
# the said to the being's stance and wakes its scheduler. The inbox is a view on its stamp.
# `wake` is grounded here. The said is the inner-Word, shown in quotes. The call is the Word.

A call is an out: a do whose word crosses to another, and holds for a word back.
The said is that word, shown in quotes — the inner word the caller speaks.
The target decides: a word to another is a call, and awaits; a word to oneself is a recall, and reads.
A do may stamp a being's body and is no call; a call wakes the being itself, that its Name may act through it.
A call makes the world after twice: once when it is sent, the ask; once when the being wakes to its own moment, and a Name acts through it, the answer.
A call may carry an intent, the why behind the said, and may be in reply to a call before it.
A being's inbox is its calls not yet seen. By its cognition the being sees them, and its Name replies.
A reply is a call back.
